-- European Union Shouldn't Play `Silly Games' on C02 Prices, IETA Head Says
-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 2010-10-04T10:16:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/european-union-shouldn-t-play-silly-games-on-c02-prices-ieta-head-says.html
European Union regulators shouldn’t
play “silly games” to push up prices for emission allowances
and should instead take a more “direct route,” said Henry
Derwent, head of the International Emissions Trading
Association, at the Carbon Show in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
